      "message": "What this `mContentDefined \u003d true` is doing is to handle this case:\n\n- Attach framebuffer to texture\n- Invalidate\n- Detach framebuffer from texture\n- Modify the texture\n- Attach framebuffer to texture again\n- Draw (with a blend, to verify previous values are LOADed)\n\nThe problem is that, while we do have a notification system such that when a framebuffer attachment is updated a certain dirty bit is set in the framebuffer, in the above scenario the texture being modified is detached from the framebuffer.\n\nIn other words, the render target of the texture remembers that it\u0027s invalidated, and when modified, it doesn\u0027t set its contents defined (because it\u0027s not attached to any framebuffer). The bug would be that the next renderpass would use DONT_CARE instead of LOAD.\n\nCould you please write a test based on this? Obviously the texture format is depth/stencil ;)",
